[Student "S"]
{This is the companion to Deal 6. The cards are the same except that the 
\Ds and \Cs have been swapped.

Again, SOUTH has no problem as long as NORTH holds at least one Key-card. 
When NORTH responds 5\C, (showing one Key-card), SOUTH can pass. 

That's what happens here.}

